<h2> Aid for Beirut&nbsp;</h2>
"First, strengthening basic services such as education, social protection and health for the Lebanese population. Secondly, we will accompany you in carrying out economic, financial and banking reforms. These reforms are fundamental for the long-term improvement of the country's overall economic situation," explained von der Leyen. According to the president, "this would allow the entrepreneurial context and the banking sector to regain the trust of the international community, thus allowing private sector investment. Lebanon needs a positive economic momentum to offer opportunities to its enterprises and its citizens,' he added.
&nbsp;
<div </div
&nbsp;
" Thirdly, security and stability are also key to investment. We will support the Lebanese military and other security forces. This will mainly concern the provision of equipment and training for border management. In addition, it would be very useful for Lebanon to conclude a working agreement with Frontex, in particular on information exchange and situational awareness," said the President of the European Commission. " Fourthly, to help you manage migration, we are committed to keeping legal paths open to Europe and reinsediating refugees from Lebanon in the EU. At the same time, we count on your good collaboration to prevent irregular immigration and combat migrant trafficking," he continued.
